1. deiectum: ac. fide: ‘apostatized' The word is thus used of ‘steadfastness overthrown' Pasas. Perp. 5 5.

r. advocatores et adsessores. Two forensis terme: ‘advocatus’ being a counsel or witness called in to the aid of a litigant; and ‘adsessor,’ exactly what the English derivative denotas, the assistant of a judge ; Sueton. Galla 143 Digest. i. ²²3 August. Coos. vi. 10.

3. Pudens. This governor may perhaps be identified with Quintus Servilius Pudens who was consul 166; Lamprid. Coram. 11. If so, his proconsulship may be dated just before that of Saturninus, cir. 178 or 179. He may, however, as the last governor mentioned by Tertullian, have been the immediate predecessor of Scapula, Δ. D. 210.
